# Handl - Cursor AI Rules
# See CODING_STANDARDS.md for full documentation

You are an expert in Next.js 16, React 19, TypeScript 5, and Tailwind CSS 4.

## Code Style
- Use functional components with hooks
- Use "use client" directive only when needed for client-side features
- Define TypeScript interfaces for all props
- Use const over let, never var
- Handle errors with try-catch blocks

## React Patterns
- Place hooks at the top of components
- Use useState for reactive state, useRef for DOM references
- Extract complex logic into custom hooks
- Use framer-motion for animations with spring transitions

## Styling
- Use Tailwind CSS utility classes
- Group classes logically: layout → spacing → colors → effects
- Use dark: prefix for dark mode variants
- Use clsx or tailwind-merge for conditional classes

## API Routes
- Use Next.js App Router (route.ts files)
- Return NextResponse.json() with proper status codes
- Validate request body before processing
- Log errors with console.error

## File Structure
- Components in /components with kebab-case filenames
- API routes in /app/api/[endpoint]/route.ts
- Use PascalCase for component names, camelCase for functions

## Naming
- Components: PascalCase (MainContent)
- Files: kebab-case (main-content.tsx)
- Functions: camelCase (handleSubmit)
- Constants: UPPER_SNAKE_CASE (EXAMPLES)
- Interfaces: PascalCase (Message)

## Best Practices
- Write self-documenting code
- Use optional chaining (?.) and nullish coalescing (??)
- Provide meaningful error messages
- Use Next.js Image for optimized images
